# abcpwn shellcheck configuration.
#
# Checked into the repo so local and CI runs enforce an identical set of
# checks regardless of which shellcheck build happens to be installed.
#
# useless-use-of-cat (SC2002) ships enabled by default in shellcheck
# 0.9.0 (the version on Ubuntu and in CI) but became opt-in from 0.11.0
# onward. Pin it on so `cat file | cmd` is flagged the same way
# everywhere -- a version drift on exactly this check once let a finding
# pass local lint while failing CI. See scripts/check-shellcheck.sh.
enable=useless-use-of-cat
